metric.label: Max Heap
metric.title: JVM Heap
metric.description: Total heap available to Elasticsearch running in the JVM.

metric.label: Used Heap
metric.title: JVM Heap
metric.description: Total heap used by Elasticsearch running in the JVM.

metric.label: Old
metric.title: GC Rate
metric.description: Number of old Garbage Collections.

metric.label: Young
metric.title: GC Rate
metric.description: Number of young Garbage Collections.

metric.label: Old
metric.title: GC Duration
metric.description: Time spent performing old Garbage Collections.

metric.label: Young
metric.title: GC Duration
metric.description: Time spent performing young Garbage Collections.

metric.label: Lucene Total
metric.title: Index Memory - Lucene 1
metric.description: Total heap memory used by Lucene for current index. This is the sum of other fields for primary and replica shards on this node.

metric.label: Stored Fields
metric.title: Index Memory
metric.description: Heap memory used by Stored Fields (e.g., _source). This is a part of Lucene Total.

metric.label: Doc Values
metric.title: Index Memory
metric.description: Heap memory used by Doc Values. This is a part of Lucene Total.

metric.label: Norms
metric.title: Index Memory
metric.description: Heap memory used by Norms (normalization factors for query-time, text scoring). This is a part of Lucene Total.

metric.label: Lucene Total
metric.title: Index Memory - Lucene 2
metric.description: Total heap memory used by Lucene for current index. This is the sum of other fields for primary and replica shards on this node.

metric.label: Terms
metric.title: Index Memory
metric.description: Heap memory used by Terms (e.g., text). This is a part of Lucene Total.

metric.label: Points
metric.title: Index Memory
metric.description: Heap memory used by Points (e.g., numbers, IPs, and geo data). This is a part of Lucene Total.

metric.label: Lucene Total
metric.title: Index Memory - Lucene 3
metric.description: Total heap memory used by Lucene for current index. This is the sum of other fields for primary and replica shards on this node.

metric.label: Fixed Bitsets
metric.title: Index Memory
metric.description: Heap memory used by Fixed Bit Sets (e.g., deeply nested documents). This is a part of Lucene Total.

metric.label: Term Vectors
metric.title: Index Memory
metric.description: Heap memory used by Term Vectors. This is a part of Lucene Total.

metric.label: Version Map
metric.title: Index Memory
metric.description: Heap memory used by Versioning (e.g., updates and deletes). This is NOT a part of Lucene Total.

metric.label: Query Cache
metric.title: Index Memory - Elasticsearch
metric.description: Heap memory used by Query Cache (e.g., cached filters). This is for the same shards, but not a part of Lucene Total.

metric.label: Request Cache
metric.title: Index Memory
metric.description: Heap memory used by Request Cache (e.g., instant aggregations). This is for the same shards, but not a part of Lucene Total.

metric.label: Fielddata
metric.title: Index Memory
metric.description: Heap memory used by Fielddata (e.g., global ordinals or explicitly enabled fielddata on text fields). This is for the same shards, but not a part of Lucene Total.

metric.label: Index Writer
metric.title: Index Memory
metric.description: Heap memory used by the Index Writer. This is NOT a part of Lucene Total.

metric.label: Search Total
metric.title: Request Rate
metric.description: Amount of search operations (per shard).

metric.label: Indexing Total
metric.title: Request Rate
metric.description: Amount of indexing operations.

metric.label: Index Time
metric.title: Indexing Time
metric.description: Amount of time spent on indexing operations.

metric.label: Index Throttling Time
metric.title: Indexing Time
metric.description: Amount of time spent with index throttling, which indicates slow disks on a node.

metric.label: Write Queue
metric.title: Indexing Threads
metric.description: Number of index, bulk, and write operations in the queue. The bulk threadpool was renamed to write in 6.3, and the index threadpool is deprecated.

metric.label: Write Rejections
metric.title: Indexing Threads
metric.description: Number of index, bulk, and write operations that have been rejected, which occurs when the queue is full. The bulk threadpool was renamed to write in 6.3, and the index threadpool is deprecated.

metric.label: Search Queue
metric.title: Read Threads
metric.description: Number of search operations in the queue (e.g., shard level searches).

metric.label: Search Rejections
metric.title: Read Threads
metric.description: Number of search operations that have been rejected, which occurs when the queue is full.

metric.label: GET Queue
metric.title: Read Threads
metric.description: Number of GET operations in the queue.

metric.label: GET Rejections
metric.title: Read Threads
metric.description: Number of GET operations that have been rejected, which occurs when the queue is full.

metric.label: CPU Utilization
metric.description: Percentage of CPU usage for the Elasticsearch process.

metric.label: Cgroup CPU Utilization
metric.title: CPU Utilization
metric.description: CPU Usage time compared to the CPU quota shown in percentage. If CPU quotas are not set, then no data will be shown.

metric.label: Cgroup Usage
metric.title: Cgroup CPU Performance
metric.description: The usage, reported in nanoseconds, of the cgroup. Compare this with the throttling to discover issues.

metric.label: Cgroup Throttling
metric.title: Cgroup CPU Performance
metric.description: The amount of throttled time, reported in nanoseconds, of the cgroup.

metric.label: Cgroup Elapsed Periods
metric.title: Cgroup CFS Stats
metric.description: The number of sampling periods from the Completely Fair Scheduler (CFS). Compare against the number of times throttled.

metric.label: Cgroup Throttled Count
metric.title: Cgroup CFS Stats
metric.description: The number of times that the CPU was throttled by the cgroup.

metric.label: Search
metric.title: Latency
metric.description: Average latency for searching, which is time it takes to execute searches divided by number of searches submitted. This considers primary and replica shards.

metric.label: Indexing
metric.title: Latency
metric.description: Average latency for indexing documents, which is time it takes to index documents divided by number that were indexed. This considers any shard located on this node, including replicas.
